  <div id="text-content_9970E930-222C-0135-DC0A-22000B5A851D" class="text-block-content">
    <p>To add a new quiz, click the <strong>Add Quiz</strong> button.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
        <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-2" id="add-classic-quiz" data-step-uuid="6a1dcfeb-7e8a-4f8d-85f2-474b816e66c2">
    <h3 id="add-classic-quiz" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Select Quiz Engine</h3>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/007/787/584/original/2ce3bc1c-9bd7-49a8-858a-790137217c1c.png" srcset="" alt="Select Quiz Engine" height="531" width="478">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_cbde4e68-add4-478d-845d-e5742b7a02fc" class="text-block-content">
    <p>If your course has New Quizzes enabled, you must select a quiz engine.</p>
<p>To select New Quizzes, click the <strong>New Quizzes</strong> option [1].</p>
<p>To create a classic quiz, click the <strong>Classic Quizzes</strong> option [2].</p>
<p>Then click the <strong>Submit</strong> button [3].</p>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> Learn more about <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-create-a-quiz-using-New-Quizzes/ta-p/1173" target="_blank">creating a quiz using New Quizzes</a>.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>
 
  </div>

